{"lemma":"حَصِيدٌ","slug":"حَصِيدٌ","root":"ح.ص.د","root_slug":"ح-ص-د","root_link":"/words/roots/ح-ص-د","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"حَصِيد","root":"حصد","pos":"N","occurrence_count":4},"wiktextract":{"found":false},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n8200"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AD%D9%8E%D8%B5%D9%90%D9%8A%D8%AF%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":null,"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n8200","headword_ar":"حَصِيدٌ","root":"HSd","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Reaped"},{"kind":"text","text":"seed-produce; (S, A, Mgh, Msb, K;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaSiyadpN","text_ar":"حَصِيَدةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Mgh, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maHoSuwdN","text_ar":"مَحْصُودٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaSadN","text_ar":"حَصَدٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaSaAdN","text_ar":"حَصَادٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", which last is originally an inf. n.: (Mgh:) pl. of the first, (A, Mgh,) and of the second, (Mgh,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaSaAy^idu","text_ar":"حَصَايِدُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (A, Mgh.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hab~u AlHaSiydi","text_ar":"حَبُّ الحَصِيدِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[see Kur l. 9]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Grain that is reaped:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"grain of wheat"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of barley"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of anything that is reaped;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as though for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hab~u Aln~aboti AlHaSiydi","text_ar":"حَبُّ النَّبْتِ الحَصِيدِ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Zj:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"grain of reaped wheat."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lth.) ―         -b2-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaSaAdN","text_ar":"حَصَادٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b3-  It is also said to signify Seed-produce"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"torn up and carried away by the wind."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L.) ―         -b4-  Also (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Slain"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mowed down"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with the sword, like seed-produce reaped."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Jel in xxi. 15.) ―         -b5-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaSaAy^idu A^alosinatihimo","text_ar":"حَصَايِدُ اَلْسِنَتِهِمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", occurring in a trad., means (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The words that their tongues utter, and"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"as it were"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"cut off, against others;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, * L;) being words wherein is no good: the tongue being likened to a reapinghook; and the words that it utters, to reaped seed-produce:"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HSAy^d","text_ar":"حصايد"},{"kind":"text","text":", here, is pl. of ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaSiydapN","text_ar":"حَصِيدَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (L.) ―         -b6-  See also what next follows."}],"source_refs":["S","Mgh","K","Msb","A","L","Zj"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}